  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;Good hospital consultants need empathy and  listening skill!&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I see several different consultants and specialisms at this hospital, and on the whole it is a good hospita and i am always listened to and treated respectfully.  However, unfortunately  i have had cause to contact PALS after a recent very poor experience at clinic appointment, where i felt disrespected and patronised and not listened to by the Consultant and the appointment actually left me quite distressed as i had waited over 9 months with many concerns and i was completely disregarded.  I emailed PALS asking how i could see someone else in that Department, no answer after over a week!!  Several phone calls just an answer machine, and no response from message left over 5 days ago.  This is VERY poor customer service particularly so with people who are vulnerable if not only by the fact they need medical care and arent getting the standard they should do.  I know PALS has moved (I tried to contact someone whilst there - also no luck!) but there is absolutely no point advertising this service for &amp;amp;quot;the advocacy of patients&amp;amp;quot; when you cant get hold of anyone and they dont respond to queries there really isnt.  For this reason i do feel this service is letting the hospital down greatly. Such service in the private sector wouldnt be seen as acceptable and so i strongly feel for a public body such as the NHS this is very unsatisfactory.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
